docs.snippet: In a quiet market in which the daily fluctuations were narrow, the dollar showed a consistently forward trend last week measured by the quotation for the French franc. From a low premium of 0.3 cent, on Monday, it rose to 0.6 cent on Thursday,...
docs.lead_paragraph: In a quiet market in which the daily fluctuations were narrow, the dollar showed a consistently forward trend last week measured by the quotation for the French franc. From a low premium of 0.3 cent, on Monday, it rose to 0.6 cent on Thursday, retaining the most of that improvement to close at 0.5 cent for a net gain of 0.1 over the previous week. Range a year ago was 81.6279.55 cents.

headline.main: FOREIGN EXCHANGE RATES; WEEK ENDED JUNE 23, 1934.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 29. -- While the trend of domestic activities in Germany, particularly these receiving government benefits, continued upward during May, the gains were powerless to reassure business sentiment, due to the foreign commercial and financial situation, the Department of Commerce said today in its weekly survey of foreign business.
